{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_67","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc \"nl -ba README.md | sed -n '1,220p'\"","aggregated_output":"     1\t# Agent Management System Prototype\n     2\t\n     3\tThis prototype is the start of a very small remote-work control plane for Codex.\n     4\t\n     5\tCurrent scope:\n     6\t\n     7\t- server-backed Codex session data in `data/agent-sessions.json`\n     8\t- one main UI at `/app/sessions`\n     9\t- background Codex session launching and follow-up prompts\n    10\t- logs, state files, and last-message capture per run\n    11\t- session APIs under `/api/agents/sessions/*`\n    12\t\n    13\t## Why this slice exists\n    14\t\n    15\tThe immediate problem is not advanced orchestration. It is having one shared place where you can:\n    16\t\n    17\t- submit a task from a browser\n    18\t- start a background Codex run on your laptop\n    19\t- see how many runs are active or finished\n    20\t- inspect logs and the last agent message\n    21\t- send a follow-up prompt into the same session later\n    22\t\n    23\tThat gives you the first useful \"work while I am away\" loop before adding auth, queueing, or richer orchestration.\n    24\t\n    25\t## Run locally\n    26\t\n    27\t```sh\n    28\tnpm install\n    29\tnpm run dev\n    30\t```\n    31\t\n    32\tValidation:\n    33\t\n    34\t```sh\n    35\tnpm run check\n    36\tnpm run lint\n    37\tnpm run test\n    38\t```\n    39\t\n    40\t## Codex sessions\n    41\t\n    42\tThe first session layer uses discrete background Codex runs:\n    43\t\n    44\t- start a run with `codex exec --json`\n    45\t- capture the discovered `thread_id`\n    46\t- send a follow-up prompt later with `codex exec resume <thread_id> --json`\n    47\t\n    48\tThis is not a browser-hosted live terminal. It is a resumable run queue with logs and last-message capture.\n    49\t\n    50\tUI:\n    51\t\n    52\t- `/app/sessions`\n    53\t\n    54\tAPI:\n    55\t\n    56\t- `GET /api/agents/sessions`\n    57\t- `POST /api/agents/sessions`\n    58\t- `GET /api/agents/sessions/:sessionId`\n    59\t- `POST /api/agents/sessions/:sessionId/messages`\n    60\t- `POST /api/agents/sessions/:sessionId/cancel`\n    61\t\n    62\tEnvironment:\n    63\t\n    64\t```sh\n    65\texport CODEX_BIN=\"$(which codex)\"\n    66\t```\n    67\t\n    68\tIf `CODEX_BIN` is not set, the prototype uses `codex` from `PATH`.\n    69\t\n    70\tSession data lives in:\n    71\t\n    72\t- `data/agent-sessions.json`\n    73\t- `data/agent-sessions/<sessionId>/runs/<runId>/`\n    74\t\n    75\tThe runner script is:\n    76\t\n    77\t- `scripts/agent-session-runner.mjs`\n    78\t\n    79\t## Recommended next steps\n    80\t\n    81\t1. Add user authentication before exposing this publicly.\n    82\t2. Add live session streaming or websocket updates instead of pure polling.\n    83\t3. Add a very small task inbox so tasks launch sessions automatically.\n    84\t4. Add deployment or secure remote access so the laptop-hosted app is reachable when you are away.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
