{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_70","type":"agent_message","text":"**Assessment**\nThis is a coherent SvelteKit prototype for a laptop-hosted Codex control plane: filesystem-backed state, a detached runner process, thin JSON APIs, and a workable `/app/sessions` UI. The shape is good for a first slice, but it is still prototype-grade and has a few structural issues that will matter quickly if you rely on it for real orchestration.\n\n**Findings**\n1. The biggest risk is unauthenticated local execution. `POST /api/agents/sessions` accepts arbitrary `cwd`, `prompt`, and `sandbox`, then launches a detached Codex run without any auth gate at all in [+server.ts:14](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/src/routes/api/agents/sessions/+server.ts#L14) and [agent-sessions.ts:282](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/src/lib/server/agent-sessions.ts#L282). The README explicitly says auth is still missing in [README.md:79](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/README.md#L79), so this is known, but it is still the dominant issue.\n\n2. Persistence is race-prone. Both stores do plain read-modify-write JSON updates with no locking or transaction boundary in [control-plane.ts:91](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/src/lib/server/control-plane.ts#L91) and [agent-sessions.ts:62](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/src/lib/server/agent-sessions.ts#L62). Concurrent heartbeats, task claims, or session starts can overwrite each other.\n\n3. Workers created from the web UI cannot authenticate to the worker API. `createWorker` defaults `authTokenHash` to `''` in [control-plane.ts:215](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/src/lib/server/control-plane.ts#L215); the `/app/workers` form persists that object directly in [+page.server.ts:54](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/src/routes/app/workers/+page.server.ts#L54); but worker API auth requires a valid hashed token in [worker-api.ts:52](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/src/lib/server/worker-api.ts#L52). So UI-created workers are effectively unusable for `/api/workers/*`.\n\n4. The sessions dashboard summary is semantically wrong once a session has multiple runs. The UI labels `completedCount` as “Finished runs” in [+page.svelte:35](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/src/routes/app/sessions/+page.svelte#L35), but `summarizeAgentSessions` counts sessions by latest status, not runs, in [agent-sessions.ts:247](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/src/lib/server/agent-sessions.ts#L247).\n\n5. Scheduling logic ignores worker `status` and `capacity`. Task availability and claiming only check role matching in [worker-api.ts:66](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/src/lib/server/worker-api.ts#L66) and [worker-api.ts:130](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/src/lib/server/worker-api.ts#L130). An offline or saturated worker can still poll and claim work.\n\n6. The app is tightly coupled to one machine. The folder picker hardcodes `/Users/colinfreed/...` roots in [+page.server.ts:20](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/src/routes/app/sessions/+page.server.ts#L20), and the seeded data file contains absolute personal paths. That is fine for a personal prototype, but it blocks portability and makes remote deployment awkward.\n\n7. Test coverage is thin. The meaningful tests are helper-level in [agent-sessions.spec.ts](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/src/lib/server/agent-sessions.spec.ts) and [worker-api.spec.ts](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/src/lib/server/worker-api.spec.ts), while UI/e2e coverage is basically “page has an h1” in [page.svelte.spec.ts:6](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/src/routes/page.svelte.spec.ts#L6) and [demo.test.ts:3](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/e2e/demo.test.ts#L3).\n\n**What’s Solid**\nThe overall separation is good: session orchestration lives in [agent-sessions.ts](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/src/lib/server/agent-sessions.ts), worker auth/queue logic in [worker-api.ts](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/src/lib/server/worker-api.ts), and the detached runner in [agent-session-runner.mjs](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/scripts/agent-session-runner.mjs). The on-disk artifact model is also sensible for debugging. README and implementation are mostly aligned.\n\nThe UI surface feels mid-transition rather than finished. There are pages for goals/tasks/workers/providers/roles, but the sidebar only exposes sessions in [Sidebar.svelte:7](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/src/lib/components/Sidebar.svelte#L7), and `/app/+page.svelte` is still a placeholder in [+page.svelte:1](/Users/colinfreed/Projects/Experiments/agent-management-system-prototype/src/routes/app/+page.svelte#L1).\n\nI did not run `npm check`, `lint`, or `test` in this pass. I also confirmed this directory is not currently a git repository, and there is no repo-local `AGENTS.md` or `.agents/skills`."}}
